title: El Salvador Consumer Price Index (CPI)
description: Consumer Price Index CPI in El Salvador increased to 125.87 points in September from 125.56 points in August of 2022. Consumer Price Index CPI in El Salvador averaged 90.79 points from 1993 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 125.87 points in September of 2022 and a record low of 48.44 points in February of 1993. In El Salvador, the Consumer Price Index or CPI measures changes in the prices paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services. This page provides - El Salvador Consumer Price Index (CPI) - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Digestyc, El Salvador
